      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 1997 Acura Integra Type R, a definitive masterpiece of 90s JDM engineering. This unit is powered by the high-revving B18C5 power plant, featuring factory-lightened connecting rods and hand-polished intake ports for superior volumetric efficiency. The engagement of the VTEC crossover remains sharp, and the close-ratio five-speed manual gearbox offers surgical precision. Mechanical integrity is absolute, featuring the original helical limited-slip differential and a reinforced chassis with factory-stiffened suspension mounting points. The Championship White paint is flawless, highlighting the aerodynamic profile and weight-optimized body panels. This is a non-modified, concours-standard example for the discerning purist.",
